programme.title: Danger Zone
programme.desc: Host Arglit Boonyai goes in search of rebels in Southern Thailand to find out what they are fighting for. In his journey he meets people who have been affected by the violence and live in constant danger.

programme.title: Danger Zone
programme.desc: Host Arglit Boonyai travels into the Fukushima exclusion zone in Japan. What is life like today and what does the future hold?

programme.title: Danger Zone
programme.desc: Host Arglit Boonyai visits Jolo in Mindanao. Its known as the 'kidnap capital' of the Philippines because of the presence of Abu Sayyaf rebels.

programme.title: Danger Zone
programme.desc: Jerusalem and the West Bank. Arguably, the world's most controversial piece of land. Meet the different parties on both sides, try to shed a bit of light on this ongoing conflict and its implications on the daily life of the people living in this region.

programme.title: Danger Zone
programme.desc: Could development be the latest obstacle to peace in fast changing Myanmar?The Shan State Human Rights Foundation alleges that the Myanmar military breached a ceasefire. This time it's not about ethnic identity or autonomy.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: For almost two centuries, tourists have been flocking to the waters of Lake Champlain hoping against the odds to glimpse the lake monster they’ve affectionately dubbed Champ. Learn about one of the oldest monster legends in the world.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: The Mothman legend captivates tourists from all over the world, who pilgrimage to Point Pleasant, West Virginia, to visit sighting locations, question locals and tour the Mothman museum or buy Mothman memorabilia. The monster is now a local celebrity.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: What is it about sleepy Adams, Tennessee, that attracts tourists eager to visit graveyards, haunted caves and cabins, swap scary stories and try to summon the spirits of the dead? The legend of the Bell Witch and a 200-year old haunting are they key.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: From the Neck Down
programme.desc: The flying doctors and paramedics of the Yorkshire Air Ambulance head to the Peak District where a mountainbiker has sustained a broken neck.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: Ice and Horses
programme.desc: The airborne medics respond when a woman is trapped in the wreckage of her car after skidding on ice, and a jockey is thrown from her horse.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: Big Falls, Bigger Breaks
programme.desc: The team spring into action when a 12-year-old boy falls 30 feet from a bridge, and a walker collapses in the Dales.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: Surprise Impalements
programme.desc: The team flies to the rescue of a driver whose car has been cut in half in a freak accident. Plus, a biker is catapulted into a wood and impaled on a branch, and a farmhand is attacked by his own cowherd.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire
Wildest Africa: Madagascar: Islands of Monsters
programme.desc: Madagascar is truly a weird and wonderful land. Isolated on an island of extreme and magical looking locations, life has adapted and diversified. With few predators, numbers have proliferated and natural selection has gone mad.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: The town of Willow Creek, California takes the legend of Bigfoot more seriously than anywhere else in the world. An ape-like monster believed to be the missing link, there are organized hunting expeditions, statues, and even a museum. But how real is it?

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: The city of Kelowna in Okanagan Valley, is home to one of Canada's oldest and most enduring legends. In the depths of Okanagan Lake, a monster known as Ogopogo, described as a 10-15 meter long serpent, has been sighted on and off since the 19th century.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: Lake Windermere, England’s largest natural lake and a popular holiday destination, is said to be the home of Bownessie: a prehistoric snake-like creature, akin to Scotland’s Loch Ness Monster. Is there any truth to the legend? We endeavor to find out.

programme.title: Caught on Camera: Gangs in the UK
programme.desc: Thugs terrorize our towns and neighborhoods, from smack dealing, to street brawling, mugging to burglary.

programme.title: Caught on Camera: Anarchy in the UK
programme.desc: Masked protesters bring mayhem to the streets of London. Shocking footage puts a rioter behind bars, and a wasted Santa experiences the perils of too much Christmas spirit.

programme.title: Caught on Camera
programme.desc: Host Nick Wallis reveals some of the street crime captured by London's 100,000 CCTV cameras: Fights, robberies, drug crimes and a massive gun rampage.

programme.title: Caught on Camera
programme.desc: This show examines the staggering rise in retail crime, both shoplifting and violence against employees, and how CCTV cameras make such a difference in apprehending the perpetrators.

programme.title: Human Prey: Killers on the Loose
programme.desc: Gary Brown's visit to an African chimp sanctuary becomes a deadly struggle when he and his guide are attacked by the colony's escaped alpha male. Idaho Zoo's 'Feast for the Beast' fundraiser takes a bloody turn when a 600-pound Siberian tiger breaks free.

programme.title: Human Prey: Killers of the Savannah
programme.desc: Focused on helping a pregnant, wounded lioness, an unarmed South African conservationist unwittingly ends up face-to-face with one of the pride's aggressive, young males. During his Zambezi River adventure, a pilot is attacked by a hungry hyena.

programme.title: Human Prey: Killer Bears
programme.desc: While hiking through Montana's Glacier National Park, Johan and Jenna Otter are attacked by a raging grizzly intent on protecting her cubs. In a remote British Columbia nature park, Patti and Kelly McConnell are mauled by a hungry 400-pound black bear.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: A 19th century legend has put the town of Rhinelander, Wisconsin on the map, a must-visit location for those interested in American folklore and the supernatural, as Rhinelander is the home of the Hodag, a mythical beast transformed into a town mascot.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: Each year, tourists with no interest in skiing or scenic views flock to the Austrian town of Klagenfurt to do a different kind of sightseeing: they’re after a glimpse of the legendary Tatzelwurm creature, or the chance to drink a beer and discuss it.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: The town of Willow Creek, California takes the legend of Bigfoot more seriously than anywhere else in the world. An ape-like monster believed to be the missing link, there are organized hunting expeditions, statues, and even a museum. But how real is it?

programme.title: Helicopter ER: Family Horror
programme.desc: A family outing ends in horror for a young mother after a seaside crash, and the flying doctors and paramedics of the Yorkshire Air Ambulance rush to find a victim's severed finger.

programme.title: Stir Of Echoes
programme.desc: After being hypnotized by his sister-in-law, a man begins seeing haunting visions of a girl's ghost and a mystery begins to unfold around him. Starring: Kevin Bacon, Zachary David Cope, Kathryn Erbe, Illeana Douglas, Kevin Dunn.

programme.title: The Heist
programme.desc: A comedy centered on three museum security guards who devise a plan to steal back the artworks to which they have become attached after they are transferred to another museum. Starring: Morgan Freeman, Christopher Walken, Joseph McKenna, Wynn Everett.

programme.title: Two Came Back
programme.desc: Susan is a seasoned sailor who agrees to help her friends bring a client's 68-foot boat from San Diego to Vancouver. After sailing the boat into a storm with disastrous consequences, the group is challenged to survive. Feat: Melissa Joan Hart.

programme.title: Christmas in Mississippi
programme.desc: Photographer Holly returns to Gulfport, Mississippi for Christmas. Their traditional holiday light show has been revived again since a hurricane struck five years earlier. She is shocked to learn the festival is run by her high school sweetheart, Mike.

programme.title: Antboy: Revenge of the Red Fury
programme.desc: With Antboy's nemesis defeated, Pelle is enjoying life as a superhero. Soon Pelle finds himself haunted, as a new super-villain announces her arrival.

programme.title: Christmas In The City
programme.desc: After closing down her family business, Wendy and her daughter move to the city for a job in the toy department. Her excitement is short lived when the store's consultant ruins the holiday spirit by replacing Santa with a male underwear model.

programme.title: Antboy
programme.desc: 12-year-old Pelle is bitten by an ant and develops superpowers. Aided by comic book nerd Wilhelm, Pelle creates a secret identity as superhero Antboy.

programme.title: Guardians of the Tomb
programme.desc: In a quest to find a lost colleague, a team of scientists find themselves deep underground in an ancient labyrinth, while trying to unearth a secret that has been buried for centuries.

programme.title: The Immigrant
programme.desc: 1921. An innocent immigrant woman is tricked into a life of burlesque and vaudeville until a dazzling magician tries to save her and reunite her with her sister who is being held in the confines of Ellis Island. Starring: Marion Cotillard, Joaquin Phoenix.

programme.title: Two Lovers
programme.desc: A Brooklyn-set romantic drama about a bachelor torn between the family friend his parents wish he would marry and his beautiful but volatile new neighbor. Starring: Joaquin Phoenix, Gwyneth Paltrow, Vinessa Shaw.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Future Zone: Future Zone

programme.title: RiffTrax Presents: Horror Express
programme.desc: The Deadly Mantis showed us that the life of a palaeontologist is one of intrigue, romance, and unstoppable monsters. Horror Express does nothing to dispel this notion, so that presumably means it can only be true.

programme.title: Rifftrax Shorts: Setting Up a Room
programme.desc: Setting Up a Room is about two women setting up a kindergarten classroom.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Alien Outlaw: Alien Outlaw
programme.desc: Predator costumes, Lash LaRue AND his fat hillbilly sidekick buddy from The Dark Power, an alien killed with a fishing hook, what more could anyone ask for. It's time for befuddlement and laughter, join Mike, Kevin and Bill for Alien Outlaw!

programme.title: RiffTrax: Maniac
programme.desc: Maniac starts when a Vaudeville-impersonator-turned-lab-assistant-to-a-mad-scientist refuses his bosses reasonable request that he shoot himself in the heart and offer his corpse as an experimental subject. After that, it starts to get strange.

programme.title: RiffTrax Presents: King of Kong Island
programme.desc: King of Kong Island is the action-packed tale of a scantily-clad jungle girl, some people who speak English without seeming to understand it and without bothering to move their lips, a mad scientist friend of theirs and their very many cigarettes.

programme.title: RiffTrax: RiffTrax Special 90s Cyber Thrillers: RiffTrax Special 90s Cyber Thrillers
programme.desc: Time to grab a stack of floppy disks, or maybe 2 of those shiny CD-ROMs we've been hearing about, and boot up the very first RiffTrax Special! The topic? 90s Cyber Thrillers.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: The Ancestor
programme.desc: Oggy is gardening peacefully when he suddenly falls into a hole and finds himself in a cave! Lost among several rock paintings, Oggy finds a big and hairy prehistoric cockroach stuck in a block of ice. It won't be long until the roaches unfreeze him!

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Ugly, Dirty and Good
programme.desc: The roaches try to break into the fridge but Oggy cuts off the cable that the insects were climbing to reach their objective. Joey falls and remains lying on the floor. But when Oggy is about to punish him, Joey smiles at him tenderly.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Just Married!
programme.desc: Jack is getting married, he chooses Oggy as his best man. Even though they haven't been invited, the cockroaches are of course attending the party! Jack gives an anti-cockroaches detector to Oggy to help him get rid of those damn insects.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories
programme.desc: Super-Noms' adventures continue! In this season, you will witness some unexpected comebacks of your favourite characters that will help Noms to fight the evil.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 7
programme.desc: In this new season, our superheroes return and so do their foes! You will see some acquaintances among the villains but their moves will be far from familiar ... However, Dr. Cheddar has something special to help Om Nom and Om Nelle in their adventures.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 8
programme.desc: Super-Noms always come to the rescue! However, in this season, rather than saving the whole city, they'll have to focus on their friends and protect them from the mischief!

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 9
programme.desc: In this season, Super-Noms will discover that superpowers are not always helpful, and that kindness, bravery, and intelligence are the real gems that can solve any situation!

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Basket Bunny / Bottle Racquet
programme.desc: Braianna is the star of her school basketball team but right in the middle of a game, she has to leave to take care of an intergalactic chicken ... / Fred wants to build a floating island made of bottles ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: The Day the Boys Stood Still / Mouse Trap
programme.desc: Fred tries to get Brains interested in his hobby – mud racing. In his attempt to convince her he awakens the demons of the mud. / Brains has to take care of Mr. Boots, a new recruit that is also a tiny mouse.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: King of the Sewer Bears / The Smelly Princess
programme.desc: Fred is named the King of the Sewer Bears due to his special birthmark. But the power is going to his head ... / Agent Brains has to protect princess Iria but her smell is so beguiling that you have to fulfil her every wish.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: The Dung Beetle / The Ride of Their Lives
programme.desc: Braianna is invited to a TV animal show but Corky is jealous and tries everything to stop her from going. / Fred and Sir Percival want to try out the new attraction in the amusement park. Friday is sad as he has to stay at home ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Return of the Dirt Demonds / The New Fred
programme.desc: Fred wants to make a monster film to impress Nora – and goes on a search for real monsters! Fred inadvertently hurts Nora with his words. He orders Friday to speak for him from now on ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Coach Dad / The Thing that Slept Over
programme.desc: Fred is not happy: His dad becomes the new gym teacher and all of Fred's classmates are exhausted! / Agent Brains investigates a slumber party to find out who has the energy-sucking leech Slimetra.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Egghead's Revenge / Surprise Day Off
programme.desc: Egghead wants to take revenge on Brains as she receives an award for being the smartest scientist. / All the teachers have been kidnapped by Potatoids – and have mutated into babies!

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Sewer Adventure!
programme.desc: Admiral Bubbles tricks Mom into believing she accidentally killed him. Horrified, she flushes him down the toilet, then quickly buys an identical fish to replace him with, hoping Beanie won't notice.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Goldfish Teriyaki!
programme.desc: A huge battle between Beanie and Admiral Bubbles in the kitchen results in the destruction of the oven. When Mom discovers this, she decides to use the money she was saving to buy a new bed to buy an oven instead.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Rescued!
programme.desc: In celebration of "Earth Day", Kevin Kelp, an ex- Greenspace activist, has converted the city's old incinerator into a recycling plant. But this is a great disappointment to Admiral Bubbles, who hates to see the old incinerator go to waste.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Stinker!
programme.desc: Inspired by the horrible mess that Beanie has cooked up for his mother's breakfast, Admiral Bubbles decides to cook up a garbage monster, bringing it to life to do his evil bidding and to terrorize the town.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Forgetful Fish!
programme.desc: Beanie and Elwood have done their school science report on earthquakes, discovering that the town is built on a fault line. Admiral Bubbles realizes that with a simple machine serving as a catalyst, he could easily destroy the entire town.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Icing On The Cake!
programme.desc: It's Beanie's birthday, and he is looking forward to his party, until he discovers that his Mom decorated the apartment in "Cute Little Bunnies". With guests starting to arrive, and certain that he will die of embarrassment, he asks the goldfish for help.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: The Secret Terractor!
programme.desc: During summer vacation, Beanie is spending two weeks on his Grandpa and Grandma's farm, and brings Admiral Bubbles along so he can keep an eye on him.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Spaceballs
programme.desc: Invincible United’s unscrupulous striker, Skarra, kidnaps the Professor and forces the fitness genius to help him outdo his enemies.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: El Sound Of Silencio
programme.desc: Supa Strikas are annihilated by Orion’s amazing airborne moves. Coach takes them to a space facility to train in a magnetic levitation chamber.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Amal Three's a Crowd
programme.desc: Rival team, Invincible United, orchestrate a fan ban for upcoming Supa Strikas matches! El Matador doesn’t think it’s a big deal, but come crunch time, he cannot perform in the empty stadium!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Bad Altitude
programme.desc: Supa Strikas get the fright of their lives upon hearing that Sultans have signed famed triplets, the Amal 3. They are said to have a psychic connection that cannot be beaten!

programme.title: Grossology: Owl Most Fowl
programme.desc: A giant Owl terrorizes the people of town and especially its pigeons.

programme.title: Grossology: Yack Attack
programme.desc: An attack on the city's water system by Sloppy Joe creates a puke-a-thon amongst the town's people.

programme.title: Grossology: Kid Rot
programme.desc: There is a new kid in school, who kind of smells. This repels most kids but attracts Ty and Abby.

programme.title: Grossology: The Greatest Race Ever Crawled
programme.desc: When the GRS-1 comes up short, Ty and Lab Rat design and build the TYMOBILE.

programme.title: Grossology: All Together Now
programme.desc: Instectiva, Lance Boil and Sloppy Joe join forces to take down the Bureau of Grossology.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Big Bo Lockdown
programme.desc: Pressure is on as Supa Strikas arrive in Spain to play Barka FC and star striker, Riano. But Shakes gets some training from Riano’s old Coach, Golare, which turns out to be less than helpful!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: The End Of Dreams
programme.desc: Big Bo helps local prison inmates by training their soccer team. But Knuckles, a nasty convict, looks just like the great goalkeeper and switches places with Big Bo! How will he escape in time for Supa Strikas’ epic game against the mighty FC Colossus?

programme.title: Supa Strikas: No 'El' in Team
programme.desc: After a mishap with the bumbling Professor, his coffee, and the state-of-the-art Match Measure Machine, things go horribly wrong with Shakes’ exercise plan!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Wolf In Coach's Clothing
programme.desc: El Matador’s selfish play causes headaches for Strikas. Coach sends him to Solinesia to learn the ancient football game that is all about teamwork. But hopes are dashed when he is banished from the country!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Communication Blok
programme.desc: Coach’s stress levels have been steadily rising ... time for some serious bed-rest and relaxation! But Supa Strikas enemies realise it’s the perfect time to send in a saboteur: One who will coach Supa Strikas as BADLY as possible!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Ball Control
programme.desc: The Blok, Supa Strikas’ solid defender, speaks only his native Brislovian. He relies on visual signals to communicate with his teammates.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Led Steppin
programme.desc: The countdown to the Super League Final has begun! Supa Strikas will fight their old rivals Invincible United. But the deceitful Vince smuggles a remote-control ball into the stadium on match day!

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Abandoned Cockroaches
programme.desc: Jack and Oggy are on a road trip, heading toward the beach. On the back seat, the roaches are making a huge mess in the car. The cats don't react: they have a plan... When they stop for gas, they abandon the roaches on the highway rest area!

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Moving Out
programme.desc: Oggy has had it with these evil roaches! This time, he's moving out! He rents an apartment downtown while the roaches stay home alone in the empty house which suddenly seems very big. Getting bored, the roaches decide to go see Oggy.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Formula 1

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Priceless Roaches

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: The Fugitive

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Invincible

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Oggy and the Magic Smile

programme.desc: Greed is one of the oldest motives for murder, and these deadly women are no exception: they’ll do anything to satisfy their need for cash. This is the dangerous world of the fortune hunters.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Sometimes, when a man and a woman unite, a terrible urge for destruction can awaken in them both. Happy couples become deadly teams, intent on one goal: murder.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: While marriage is meant to be for life, it often ends in divorce. These wives took their marriages vow seriously: "till death do us part.".

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: These women never get their hands dirty: no blood touched them because they manipulate others to kill for them...but they didn't get away.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Women who kill husbands, lovers, rivals and parents will shock society. But a very special horror is reserved for women who will kill their own.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: A lovely lady with an innocent smile, kind eyes, a charming personality? No one would suspect a woman like that would murder. These women don’t look or behave like killers.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The heaviest judgments of convicted killers are reserved for those who committed premeditated murder. These women plot and plan. They know the consequences of their actions, but still they go forward to kill.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Under His Control
programme.desc: These are love stories with bleak, bloody endings. Blinded by desire, obsessed and malleable, some women fall into lethal relationships with dangerous, controlling men.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Secrets and Lies
programme.desc: Behind their friendly smiles, deadly women hide histories of bloodshed and murder.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Killing Spree
programme.desc: In 1984, in South Florida, a rapist and murderer was on the loose. The killer was a ruthless and terrifying predator, the newest member of an infamous group known as serial killers.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Melissa Brannen: Missing
programme.desc: In 1989, residents of a close-knit apartment community in Virginia gathered for a holiday celebration. For Tammy Brannen and five-year-old daughter Melissa, Christmas was always a special time. Then, without warning, the little girl was gone.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Unabomber
programme.desc: For nearly two decades a mathematical genius with delusions of single-handedly destroying industrial society, planted or mailed powerful bombs to unsuspecting innocent victims.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Murdering Cowboy
programme.desc: The sun set on the Wild West long ago, but some people refused to notice. Claude Dallas was one of them. A wily trapper, Dallas typified the rugged individualism that forged this country. He went too far when he killed two game wardens in 1981.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The World Trade Center Bombing
programme.desc: Terrorist bombings are what happen in other countries. Not here in the United States. And yet, in 1993, it happened in New York City.

programme.title: The FBI Files: John Gotti: Convicted
programme.desc: John Gotti was ambitious, powerful and ruthless. He ruled with flash and conspicuous style, playing celebrity with the media and cat and mouse with the FBI. They called John Gotti the Teflon Don. Serious charges just wouldn't stick.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The True Story of Mississippi Burning
programme.desc: Philadelphia, Mississippi, 1964. A sleepy southern town steeped in tradition finds itself targeted for invasion.

programme.title: The FBI Files: A Model Killer
programme.desc: It's a model's job to rivet the public's attention. But in 1984, some aspiring models began attracting publicity in a terrible new way.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Hired Gun
programme.desc: When three people were found murdered in their home, it appeared like a burglary gone awry. But a crime this horrific deserved a closer look.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Cat and Mouse
programme.desc: He was a predator, abducting girls and young women from their own front yards in broad daylight. He was a sadist: phoning one victim's family, taunting them, boosting then dashing their hope, and he wouldn't stop until we stopped him.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Cracking The Cartel
programme.desc: A mother and child are kidnapped, a bystander is murdered. Violence such as this shattered a quiet Texas neighborhood and exposed a drug cartel that flourished where it was least expected.

programme.title: The FBI Files: A Stranger in Town
programme.desc: She appeared on the highway in the spring, a young woman, her life cut short, her past and her identity a mystery. Only by finding out who she was could we ever hope to find her killer.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Master Plan
programme.desc: Willow Springs, Illinois, seemed like any other quiet Midwestern community. But it was really one of the most corrupt places in the nation. This tiny village, nestled just outside of Chicago, was in the hip pocket of organized crime.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Firefight
programme.desc: In Miami, a gang of robbers targeted banks and armored cars. They carried assault weapons and weren't afraid to use them. They struck during the day, and sometimes twice a day. For awhile, they seemed unstoppable.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Killer Abroad
programme.desc: Beginning in 1990, Europe found itself in the clutches of a serial killer. He became an international outlaw, hopping from country to country to evade capture and to kill again.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Moving Target
programme.desc: When a sniper in Utah started targeting African-American men for death, authorities launched a massive investigation. With scant clues and no witnesses they found the odds stacked against them, and they had no idea where the killer would strike next.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Mission
programme.desc: When a family was murdered in Arkansas, it seemed like an isolated event. But soon the crime was revealed to be part of an ever-widening circle of violence that defined a new age of domestic terrorism.

programme.title: The FBI Files
programme.desc: In 1995, our nation's capital was also our nation's murder capital. Even the police weren't safe. While Washington, DC, law enforcement targeted criminals, the criminals targeted law enforcement, even gunning down officers on patrol.

programme.title: The FBI Files: .22 Caliber Killer
programme.desc: In Buffalo, New York, a sniper targeted African-American men. He held a city hostage, and threatened to ignite a racial powder keg. And it looked like others might be following his bloody example.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Driven to Kill
programme.desc: A serial rapist targeted women. His dark urges raged out of control and led him to murder. He followed a path so random it was impossible to trace, and all that tied him to his crimes were his access to the highways and a bizarre sexual fetish.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Obsession
programme.desc: Power is a responsibility as well as a privilege. But in the wrong hands, power can corrupt. For former Deputy Attorney General for the State of Delaware, losing sight of his sworn oath to uphold justice could prove lethal.

programme.title: The FBI Files: First and Kennedy Street Crew
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Terror In Disguise
programme.desc: Banks use a variety of devices to discourage would-be robbers: security cameras, silent alarms, and exploding dye packs. But when an elusive bank robber targeted Seattle's banks, none of these precautions were effective.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Trail
programme.desc: The disappearance of young women triggered a search that spanned the Pacific Northwest. A massive media campaign failed to locate the drifter, who first charmed then killed them. As investigators followed his trail, he always stayed one step ahead.

programme.title: Surfing Elite (2013)
programme.desc: Surfing Elite The Pro Tape is a surfing movie dedicated to the biggest names in professional surfing. This is the Surfing Elite. These are the shakers and movers of our sport and for good reason.

programme.title: Volcom Stone Presents: BS! (2014)
programme.desc: BS! is an out of the ordinary, if not extraordinary surf film that documents the serious ripping of Dusty Payne, Mitch Coleborn, Alex Gray, Ozzie Wright, Nate Tyler, and Andrew Doheny.

programme.title: Surfing Presents: Du Ciel
programme.desc: This stunning piece of cinema celebrates everything we love about the ocean, including its raw power and ability to put man in his place.

programme.title: Surfer Girlz - Heat Wave
programme.desc: Surfer Girlz Heat Wave interviews the world's best women surfers and even surfing legend Kelly Slater.

programme.title: Surf Skate
programme.desc: What does surfing and skating have in common? If you said, "sick airs" then you would be correct! Surf Skate - Above-the-Lip has plenty of mental surfing and skating airs.

programme.title: Surf Rider Single Fin
programme.desc: Witness some of the most stylish and smile filled rides ever. A classic longboard surf movie for all ages to enjoy. Filmed in high definition with both land and water angles.

programme.title: Surf One
programme.desc: Surf One explores the life and experiences of a tribe of surfers who search for the perfect wave and look to pass the stoke of surfing on to the younger generation.

programme.title: Stoked and Broke
programme.desc: A staycation Surfari Epic on Zero Dollar. Making their own boards, bamboo rickshaws, solar cookers, and hobo stoves, surfers Ryan Burch and Cyrus Sutton set off on a thirty mile, eight day walk through San Diego, CA.

programme.title: Shack Therapy
programme.desc: Shack up around the world as the crew explores South Africa, Hawaii, Norway, Mexico, Caroline Islands, and West Oz. Travel in Brian Conely's Hurricane Hunter to desolate Baja breaks.

programme.title: One California Day
programme.desc: Follow the lives of eight California surfers in One California Day. Produced by Build Worldwide, and Co-Directed by Mark Jeremias (maker of Drive) and Jason Baffa (maker of Singlefin Yellow).

programme.title: Children of the Wind
programme.desc: Children of the Wind tells the story of the Bonaire windsurfers, a group of native Caribbean kids, who under the mentorship of Elvis Martinus, founder of the Bonaire Aquaspeed windsurfing club, overcame insuperable odds.

programme.title: 1000 Waves to Surfing Glory
programme.desc: 1000 Waves to Surfing Glory is presented in a dream like structure with no distracting titles letting the visual imagery speak freely to your surfing soul and wanderlust.

programme.title: Chill: Crashed Ice Tour, Canada & Leo Slemett
programme.desc: Chill moves to the winter sports this week as we head to Niagara Falls, Canada where they are hosting the opening round of the Crashed Ice Tour.

programme.title: Chill: Wakeboarding Legend, Harley Clifford & Kiteboarding Elite, Liam Whaley
programme.desc: This week on CHILL we take a tour through one of the world's best board sports on the water with Harley Clifford. And we witness kiteboarding at its elite level with Spain's Liam Whaley and others.

programme.title: Chill: Cold Water Classic, Canada & World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia
programme.desc: Jarrad Howse takes Chill to the hidden surfing destination of Tofino in Canada. Cold, wet and windy but better yet, sublime surf! We catch up with the Pro's at the Cold Water Classic.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Women's Waterski Jumping, Australia & World Cup Waterski Slalom, Indonesia
programme.desc: This week on Chill, it's water skiing around the world, we're at the jumping in Australia and the slalom in Palembang. We check out PKRA Mexico, then catch up with surfing sensations, Courtney Cologue and Sage Erickson.

programme.title: Chill: Swatch Girls Pro, France & Kite Foil Gold Cup, Mexico
programme.desc: Chill heads to France to follow some of the biggest names in women's Surfing for a day of relaxation. An inside look at the technique needed to perform at the highest level in Kitesurfing. And we Chill with Japanese surf star Izuku Tanaka.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Indonesia & Longboard Pro Circuit, China
programme.desc: We look at the skills required and the thrills delivered by the wave that stands as the king of them all - the mighty Barrel. The Longboard Pro Circuit in China is our next destination where we hang out with Kassia Meador and Darcy Liu..

programme.title: Chill: Swatch Pro Tour, France & World Cup Waterski Jumping, Australia
programme.desc: Chill joins the girls of the Swatch Pro Tour in South West France, the top riders and local talent in the freestyle section of the PKRA event in Mexico and the men of world cup waterski jumping in Australia.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia & Kitesurfing World Tour, Italy
programme.desc: The very best in Women's wakeboarding as the IWWF comes to Mandurah in Australia. The beautiful Italian Island of Sicily plays host to the Kitesurfing world Tour.

programme.title: Chill: Action Sports Game, Australia & Women's World Longboard Championship, China
programme.desc: Chill heads down under for some water ski-jumping with the Men's Action Tricks Comp and Women's Ski Jump. We take an in-depth look at the Women's longboard Championships in the South China Sea.

programme.title: Chill: Waterski Jump Legend, Freddy Krueger & Women Longboard Professionals, China
programme.desc: This week we will travel to Western Australia to catch up with the Waterski Jump Legend Freddy Krueger. Style, elegance and a hard edge of competition combine in China as we watch some of the best women longboard professionals.

programme.title: Chill: World Kitesurfing Champion, Youri Zoon
programme.desc: Chill heads to Rio to follow some of the biggest names in the Surfing arena. An inside look with World Kitesurfing Champion Youri Zoon and an intimate training session with a bunch of Wakeboarders.

programme.title: Chill: Freddy Krueger, Wakeboard World Cup Australia
programme.desc: Freddy "The Nightmare" Krueger is the undisputed ski jumping legend. Chill gets up close and personal to discover his drive and passion which ultimately keeps him striving for perfection.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia & Kitesurfing World Tour, Morocco
programme.desc: We are on the waters of Mandurah, Australia for the men's finals at the IWWF Wakeboard World. Morocco is our next destination for the kitesurf world tour, and we profile Harley Clifford.

programme.title: Minds in the Water
programme.desc: The story of one surfer's international journey to help protect dolphins, whales and their ocean environment. Shot on location in Australia, the Galapagos, Chile and Japan, it captures a key moment in one person's life when apathy is no longer an option.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Missing Person
programme.desc: Tragedy unfolds at Westbrook Beach when lifeguards are unable to locate a missing man. The man will be deemed lost at sea if he isn’t found soon, so senior lifeguard Ant takes charge.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: The Festive Season Kicks Off
programme.desc: Durban, South Africa is a hot spot for vacationers during the busy summer season. The season starts on high alert when senior lifeguard Sihle rescues a bather caught in a rip current.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Busiest Day of the Year
programme.desc: New Year’s is the busiest day of the year in Durban. Crowds arrive in hopes that the sea, soft sand and sunshine will cure their hangovers. It's a day of frivolity and endless mishaps.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Powercraft
programme.desc: It's December 31 — a good day for lifeguard trainee Penny to face her fear of big waves. All eyes are on her as she paddles into some of the biggest waves of the season.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Mass Rescue
programme.desc: There's pandemonium at the Wedge when a flash rip sweeps 150 bathers — most of whom can’t swim — off of the sand bank and into deep, treacherous water.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: African Christmas
programme.desc: The fun and festivity of Christmas Day are put on hold after a mass blue bottle jellyfish attack. Lifeguards are forced to close Battery Beach and Country Club.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Day of Reconciliation
programme.desc: The Day of Reconciliation — the first big public holiday of the festive season — starts off damp and overcast. Undeterred, 150,000 vacationers flock to the beaches.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Shark Attack
programme.desc: Five bathers are bitten by an unknown sea creature at the Bay of Plenty, breaking the festive mood and creating a mass panic. Could this be a shark attack?

programme.title: Christmas from Hollywood
programme.desc: A look at how Hollywood has portrayed Christmas, featuring the Hollywood Christmas parade, clips from movies about Santa Claus and Christmas, Christmas carols sung by movie stars and more.

programme.title: Laurel & Hardy: Hog Wild
programme.desc: Hog Wild is a 1930 American pre-Code Laurel and Hardy film, directed by James Parrott.

programme.title: The Glen Campbell Goodtime Hour: Christmas Special (December 21, 1969)
programme.desc: The Glen Campbell Goodtime Hour Christmas 1969. Celebrate the holiday season with country music superstar Glen Campbell and his pals.. Featuring Andy Griffith, Cher and more!

programme.title: The Adventures Of Sherlock Holmes
programme.desc: Holmes is threatened by a man sentenced to death stating he will kill Holmes before he is executed.

programme.title: Laurel & Hardy: Below Zero
programme.desc: Stan and Ollie have a streak of back luck after their instruments get smashed.

programme.title: Gumby's Christmas Capers
programme.desc: Join everybody s favorite playmates as they bring a world of Christmas adventure to life in these wonderful, stop-action holiday stories….

programme.title: Shirley Temple
programme.desc: Nathaniel Hawthorne's supernatural and romantic tale of a New England family and their life in the House of the Seven Gables, a two-hundred-year-old dwelling haunted by the ghosts of past generations.

programme.title: Laurel & Hardy: Busy Bodies
programme.desc: Stan and Ollie battle inanimate objects, coworkers, and the laws of physics in a sawmill.

programme.title: Father Knows Best: The Christmas Story
programme.desc: In an attempt to remind his family of the real meaning of Christmas, Jim decides the Andersons will cut down their own Christmas tree this year.

programme.title: Laurel & Hardy: Blotto

programme.desc: Teenaged mother Rachel Timmerman takes her 1-year-old on a date with a mystery man, and never returns. When her body is finally discovered in a muddy lake, the FBI goes on a desperate search to figure out who murdered the young woman….

programme.title: Alaska State Troopers: Moose/Man Hunt
programme.desc: From Alaska's toughest cities to its farthest reaches, troopers are on the hunt for armed and dangerous criminals as well as an abandoned moose, shot illegally by an eager hunter.

programme.title: Alaska State Troopers: Gun N Hide
programme.desc: When troopers respond to a call regarding a discharged gun in the Mat-Su Valley, they discover a large stash of weapons hidden inside a boat.

programme.title: Alaska State Troopers: Midnight Poachers
programme.desc: This hour-long journey with the "Alaska State Troopers" gives you a front-row seat into the work of the first response in the last frontier, where suspects and beasts alike could be lurking around every corner.

programme.title: Crime Scene Solvers: The Savage Murder of a Mother and her Daughter (Amato Case)
programme.desc: On March 31, 2003, firefighters were called to a fire in a housing estate of Meyrargues, near Aix-en-Provence. On site, they discovered a horrific scene: the tortured and charred bodies of a mother and her daughter, Chantal and Audrey D'Amato.

programme.title: Crime Scene Solvers: A Night of Horror at Devil's Plateau (Marie-Jeanne Meyer Case)
programme.desc: On June 18, 2011, Marie-Jeanne Meyer, 17-years old, waved goodbye to her sister before leaving for her daily jog on the heights of Tournon in Ardèche. Three days later, her mutilated body was found in a freshly dug pit, near an area known to be cursed.

programme.title: Crime Scene Solvers: A Mysterious Murder at the Farm (Vale´rie Bary Case)
programme.desc: On Friday, March 26, 2004, in the region of Dijon, Laurent Bary came home from his work to discover the lifeless body of his wife, Valerie, bathing in a pool of blood.

programme.title: Exhibit A: Killer in a Box
programme.desc: In 1986, Toronto and the rest of Canada were stunned by the Alison Parrott case. More than a decade would pass before this tragic case would be solved thanks to the perseverance of the newly formed “Cold Case Squad.”.

programme.title: Exhibit A: Sky High
programme.desc: A quiet May evening is shattered by the blast of a huge explosion and minutes later part of a quiet urban neighbourhood is up in flames. The police are confronted with hate slogans spray-painted onto what is left of a garage door.

programme.title: Exhibit A: Suspicion
programme.desc: An Ottawa journalist champions early parole for a convicted murderer and in the tradition of a cheap romance novel, ends up falling in love with him. After he’s released, the two move in together. Then she mysteriously disappears.

programme.title: Exhibit A: Fabric of Lies
programme.desc: A three and a half-year-old child is reported missing. After a 20-day search, her body is found floating in Toronto harbour. Fibre evidence found throughout the child’s clothes plays a crucial role in solving this crime and convicting a child killer.

programme.title: Exhibit A: Tragedy of Errors
programme.desc: “Tragedy of Errors” focuses on the forensic skills of two blood spattering experts. As the story unfolds we witness how these investigators are able to decipher a story from bloodstain patterns the way archaeologists read ancient hieroglyphics.

programme.title: Exhibit A: Killer Gloves
programme.desc: An intruder breaks into a family home in a well-to-do Calgary neighbourhood. When he’s confronted by the owner, the burglar stabs him to death. The killer flees leaving behind several smudged prints on a window that appear to be left by a pair of gloves.

programme.title: Exhibit A: Dead Sea
programme.desc: A fisherman, trawling off the English coast, comes upon what appears to be a large fish in his net. But it turns out to be a dead body. The body is wearing shoes and a Rolex watch, but has no I.D. – is it murder or suicide?

programme.title: Exhibit A: The Trouble With Susan
programme.desc: A woman is reported missing. It takes nearly 2 weeks for the police to determine that this is no missing person case. The homicide squad slowly amasses enough evidence to charge a man with murder even though the victim’s body still has not been found.

programme.title: Outlaw Empires
programme.desc: The Crips were founded in South Central L.A. on the principles of self-protection and pride. But insiders tell a story of escalating turf battles, danger, violence – and ever-diminishing unity – as the gang grew in size and power.

programme.title: Outlaw Empires
programme.desc: An unexpected outgrowth of the racial desegregation of the late 1960s, the Aryan Brotherhood had its origins in American prisons, where inmates joined forces to protect themselves from other racial groups.

programme.title: Outlaw Empires
programme.desc: From the 1800s to the early 1970s, Irish street gangs waged war for control of Boston’s underworld. By 1972, they had called a truce. One man, James “Whitey” Bulger, emerged from that truce to become a lethal and legendary force.

programme.title: Outlaw Empires
programme.desc: They’re the most notorious crime empire of all time, bound by profound bonds of blood and family.

programme.title: 72 Hours: Monster of Miramichi
programme.desc: Firemen are called to a blaze and discover two sisters, one dead and the other on death's door. Detectives learn that a man snuck in and brutally sexually assaulted the sisters before setting fire to the house.

programme.title: 72 Hours: The Violinist
programme.desc: Surgically clean body parts start turning up on a highway. Stranger still, they have been drained of every drop of blood.

programme.title: 72 Hours: Betrayed
programme.desc: 19 year old Greg Parsons is convicted of brutally murdering his mother mainly on evidence of the audio tape of a song he'd written, "Kill your Parents".

programme.title: 72 Hours: The Great Despisers
programme.desc: A 19 year old man comes home one night to discover that his family had all been savagely murdered. Could it be the insurance money and a movie called "The Great Despisers" that motivated the killers to perpetrate such violence?

programme.title: 72 Hours: Faith Healer
programme.desc: A trucker at a roadside rest station discovers the fully clothed body of a dead East Indian woman.

programme.title: Hollidaysburg
programme.desc: A former prom king and his high school classmate begin an unlikely romance when they return from college on their first holiday break. From the filmmakers behind BREAKUP AT A WEDDING.

programme.title: The Humbling
programme.desc: A stage actor who is slowly losing his mind engages in a relationship with a sexually confused younger woman. Starring: Al Pacino, Greta Gerwig, Nina Arianda.

programme.title: Slightly Single in LA
programme.desc: Dale Squire is a hip, quirky, independent single gal living in the glossy city of Los Angeles. After several failed attempts in quasi-relationships, Dale concludes that finding a meaningful relationship in L.A. is impossible. Starring: Lacey Chabert.

programme.title: A Month of Sundays
programme.desc: Miserable real estate agent Frank, whose business is failing and his relationship with his family is at an all-time low, meets by chance Sarah, a nice woman who reminds him of his mother. Their friendship starts healing him emotionally.

programme.title: Free State
programme.desc: Loosely based on William Shakespeare’s Romeo & Juliet, Free State is set in 1970’s South Africa. A time when it was against the law to have interracial relations. Starring: Nicola Breytenbach, Andrew Govender, Leleti Khumalo.

programme.title: Love on the Side
programme.desc: A small-town waitress vies with a sassy city slicker for the attention of the town's most eligible bachelor.

programme.title: Love Under The Stars
programme.desc: When a 30-something woman living in an infinite state of youth is finally forced out into the real world, she befriends a young girl and a widower that will teach her that it is okay to grow up.

programme.title: A Month of Sundays
programme.desc: Miserable real estate agent Frank, whose business is failing and his relationship with his family is at an all-time low, meets by chance Sarah, a nice woman who reminds him of his mother. Their friendship starts healing him emotionally.

programme.title: Twelve Trees Of Christmas
programme.desc: Starring Lindy Booth, Melanie Brown, and Robin Dunne. Cheri rallies her Manhattan neighborhood to participate in a Christmas tree contest when their local library is abruptly set for demolition by an ambitious but handsome developer. Feat: Mel B.

programme.title: My Bakery in Brooklyn
programme.desc: Two cousins, two kinds of thinking, and a bakery for saving.

programme.title: A Random Encounter
programme.desc: What seems to be a chance encounter one day at a coffee shop leads to a full-fledged romance, but the couple must fight for their relationship to survive the craziness that is show business. Starring: Meghan Markle, Sean Young, Michael Rady.

programme.title: Love Me Like You Do
programme.desc: Katherine Heigl and Ben Barnes star in this sweeping romance about finding love in the least likely of places! He is a travelling musician, and she is a fallen country music star who is a recently single mother, battling to hold on to her young daughter.

programme.title: Some Girls
programme.desc: On the eve of his wedding, a successful writer travels across the country to meet up with ex-lovers in an attempt to make amends for past relationship transgressions. Starring: Adam Brody, Kristen Bell, Zoe Kazan.

programme.title: Cop Dog
programme.desc: After Robby's father is killed during police duty, Robby teams up with his dad's old police dog, Marlowe. Together they must solve the crime Robby's dad never got to finish.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Dreamer
programme.desc: It is through our wildest dreams that we achieve new knowledge. We see dreams of feeding the world with insects, dreams of a synthesis of the fundamental theories of physics, and dreams of our future as extra-terrestrials.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Searcher
programme.desc: We keep expanding our knowledge, and sometimes we know exactly what we are looking for. Patterns in apparent chaos, new elements or a key for translating old and forgotten languages. We are sure they exist.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Player
programme.desc: Humans and animals play and this renders them familiar with their environments. We zoom in on scientists who combine play and mathematics, and see how playing with matter yields new materials with special properties.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Thinker
programme.desc: Our brains are constantly aware of our place in reality. How does this work for animals? Does an objective reality even exist, and does it leave any room for something like god? Where will our thinking lead us?

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Connector
programme.desc: Humankind, society and technology are dramatically influenced by science. In this episode we connect all the knowledge of The Mind of the Universe in an overarching outlook on the future. What is the future of humanity, society, and knowledge?

programme.desc: Moon and Gloom / Universal Changes / Unearthly Circumstances / The Human Body Transformed.

programme.title: What If
programme.desc: Out-of-This-World Experiences / Worst-Case Scenarios / Water World / Animals Make the Earth Go Round.

programme.title: What If
programme.desc: Our Planet Done Differently / The Impossible Becoming Possible / Mother Nature’s Revenge / Humans and the Environment / Adventures Waiting to Happen.

programme.title: Tornado Chasers: Liftoff
programme.desc: The new chase season launches as Reed and the crew add a third Dominator to the fleet.

programme.title: Tornado Chasers: Legends
programme.desc: Jim Cantore, famed meteorologist and Reed's hero, arrives in Norman to chase in the Doms. With severe weather in the forecast, Reed connects with his team members, including a wavering Joel Taylor.

programme.title: Tornado Chasers: Helix
programme.desc: The chase season roars to life as two Kickstarter backers, Ray and Bill, join the TVN team. Reed and his crew observe a rare and dramatic tornado, along with the destruction it leaves behind.

programme.title: Tornado Chasers: Payback
programme.desc: After Reed's success the day before, Dick abandons the TVN team and goes rogue. With an outbreak brewing in Kansas, Reed makes a risky move to chase in Oklahoma.

programme.title: Tornado Chasers: Warning: Part 1
programme.desc: With twisters targeting the OKC metro area, Jim Cantore joins forces with Reed to provide real-time warnings. A breakneck chase through the populated city of Edmond leads to the team's first intercept in Dominator 3.

programme.title: Tornado Chasers: Warning: Part 2
programme.desc: The unrelenting chase continues as Reed, Jim Cantore, and the team intercept another tornado before it grows into a mile-wide wedge. Coming upon storm damage, they perform search and rescue as a new tornado forms near Shawnee, OK.

programme.title: Tornado Chasers: Home: Part 1
programme.desc: Reed's tornado intercepts gain national attention as the TVN team gears up for a stronger round of severe weather. Ginger Zee joins Reed and Jim Cantore for a chase day that threatens the city of Moore, OK.

programme.title: Tornado Chasers: Home: Part 2
programme.desc: A devastating tornado tracks through Moore, OK, very close to Reed's house. Reed and the team, along with Jim Cantore and Ginger Zee, must decide whether to continue chasing or return to Moore.

programme.title: Tornado Chasers: Stranded
programme.desc: Reed and the team journey north to Kansas and come face-to-face with a mile-wide wedge.

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: The Origins of Africa
programme.desc: Africa is Mother Earth. Gondwana, the first, single, landmass broke apart into today's continents, but its heart is Africa. Land of rifts, lakes and volcanoes, Africa's mineral deposits testify to its eons-old history.

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: Africa Today
programme.desc: Volcanic activity and climate change define Africa's modern geological history. Recently meaning 50 million years ago the Arabian plate snapped off the African continent and joined Southeast Asia.

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: North America
programme.desc: North America's physical features were formed by volcanic eruptions, earthquakes and an ice age. To understand the geological forces at play, we look at the Rockies, the Grand Canyon and Canadian Shield. Also - will part of California become an island?

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: Central America
programme.desc: Central America takes us back to when the world was young. A fragile line of islands linking North and South America, the islands of the Caribbean are recent apparitions on earth and may not be here to stay.

programme.title: Voyage of the Continents: South America
programme.desc: One glance at a map of South America says it all: Andes and Amazonian basin. Two huge geological characteristics that describe how the continent came into being. The Amazon was once under the sea.

programme.title: Catalyst: Tattoos, Moon Mining, Muscle Fiber

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Next Stop Mars
programme.desc: Mars has fired our imagination for thousands of years. The tantilizing possibility of life has made it the most inviting planet in our solar system. It is the only other place that man may one day call home.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: The Planet Makers
programme.desc: From the beginnings of our solar system 4.5 billions years ago, there remain many clues to reveal its evolution. Remnant debris, asteroids, and comets are what's left of the building blocks to our celestial neighborhood.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: The Gas Giants
programme.desc: In the cold, dark expanse of our solar system, beyond the asteroid belt, lie the giant planets. Some can be seen with the naked eye, others have been visited by our camera. What secrets do they hold?

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: The Moons of Olympus
programme.desc: There are many more worlds in our solar system than just the planets. The mysterious moons of the gas giants may hold much more than we ever imagined. Each one is unique, and each one deserves a scrutinous eye.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: The Sun
programme.desc: The sun bathes our planet in warmth and light. It powers the machinery of nature, our weather, and it encourages and sustains life on land and at sea. We study it closely, and it can reveal the secrets of all other stars.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Exo Planets
programme.desc: As scientists and astronomers peer more closely and with evermore fidelity at nearby stars, they are discovering countless exo planets. How many Earth-like planets are out there? Could one of them hold life not so different from our own?

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Edge of the Universe
programme.desc: The night sky is a time machine. The further we look out into the universe, the further back in time we reach. Most of what we see is actually dark matter and dark energy, but its nature eludes us ... for the moment.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: The Astronauts
programme.desc: Who are these people that venture into space? Once they were test pilots, then scientists and engineers now teachers, politicians and paying tourists what does it take to earn the astronaut wings?

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Space: Getting There
programme.desc: The new surge in space transportation, privately owned companies vying for government contracts and private entrepreneurs looking to build hotels in space.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Orbit
programme.desc: Chances are, you are watching this program by satellite, one way or the other. Every day we use these wonders of human design, from communication and weather observation, to GPS and recourse management.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Shore to Shore
programme.desc: With low Earth orbit delegated to private companies, NASA is free to develop the deep space hardware for missions to Mars and beyond. The Orion space craft and SLS launch system are well on their way to delivering this capability.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Mars: Adapt or Leave
programme.desc: Air, water, food, electricity and fuel all the essentials to explore the solar system, this episode explores the innovative plans for astronauts to grow their own food and extract water and fuel at their destinations.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: First Light
programme.desc: The Hubble Telescope is nearing its end, the replacements are ready to go, ready to peer further back in time and space than can be imagined.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Stars Above
programme.desc: The life cycle of stars reveal to us the past and the future of Earth and ourselves.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: The Dark Side
programme.desc: In terms of the Universe, we know we don't know much, especially when it comes to dark matter and dark energy. Scientists are devoting so much of their time to discovering as much as the possibly can about this mysterious matter.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Living with Space
programme.desc: Astronauts and Cosmonauts train and study for years to work and live aboard the International Space Station. With this wealth of experience and insight behind them what do they think when they return to Earth?

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Atmosphere
programme.desc: Our atmosphere is an unbelievably complex machine that protects us from the vacuum of space, shelters us from harmful radiation and allows us and the biosphere to breath; we need to learn much more about it so we can better it.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Flight Status
programme.desc: The next 12 months will see an intense rise in flight tests, demonstration launches and high priority flights. Some are on time others are not. We check the flight status of some of this new hardware and these new capabilities.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Invasion Mars
programme.desc: For over 50 years we have bombarded Mars with our probes and landers. Spying from orbit to map terrain, finding her strengths and weaknesses. The time nearing for the full scale invasion of the planet- when humans walk on Mars and claim it for their own.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Juno, Cassini and Beyond
programme.desc: The Amazing Cassini spacecraft and its sibling lander, Huygens, have now concluded their scientific studies, bringing back years of data. Now, Juno piercing the cloak of Jupiter and her distant relative New Horizons at the edge of the solar system.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Sling Shot
programme.desc: Soviet Luna 3 was the first to use gravity to change course to photograph the dark side of the Moon. NASA Mariner 10 used the technique to swing by Venus to target Mercury. The gravity sling shot maneuver has become a standard for space navigation.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Living Planet
programme.desc: We have been observing Earth for 40 years now, in the last 20 we have focus with intensity on the planet with new technologies and capabilities, we have accumulated a mass of data that is now revealing a complex and ever changing living planet.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Cosmic Collisions
programme.desc: Space is vast, yet it is full of collisions. Gas and dust electrostatically flock together, and gravity takes over coalescing grains into rocks. Those rocks become boulders, then asteroids colliding again and again, striking planets and each other.

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration
programme.desc: Project Gemini Commences - Did Gemini give the US a lead in the space race? Venus Express - The last days of ESA's Venus probe. EMU - NASA's Extravehicular Mobility Unit. Deep Space Communications - ESA's worldwide network of giant dishes.

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration
programme.desc: Project Gemini Advances - NASA refines the techniques needed for rendezvous. Cassini at Saturn - In the Cassini probe's final years of activity, its handlers are asking it to do more complex and risky assignments.

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration
programme.desc: Project Gemini: Docking and EVA - In the final phase of the Gemini program NASA struggles with docking and spacewalks. Curiosity Roving Mars - On the surface of Mars the Curiosity rover is changing the way we think about the red planet.

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration
programme.desc: The Apollo Program Begins - At the very beginning of NASA's moon project things go wrong. Caves - ESA's special training program for astronauts. Planck - Mapping the cosmic microwave background radiation.

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration
programme.desc: Rebuilding Project Apollo - After the Apollo 1 disaster NASA resumes manned space flight. Orbiting Carbon Observatory 2 - Monitoring the Earth's Co2 levels in unprecedented detail. Zero Gravity Training - Parabolic flights.

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration
programme.desc: Beyond Earth Orbit - The Apollo program takes bold new steps. IXV Re-entry Vehicle - Europe is working to perfect a re-entry vehicle. Galileo Satellites Lost and Found - Navigation satellites go into incorrect orbit.

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration
programme.desc: To the Moon - The Apollo program achieves its major objective. Dragon, Falcon and Spacex - New directions in re-usable spacecraft. Gaia- Mapping our galaxy in unprecedented detail.

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration
programme.desc: The Beginning of the End - After the first Moon landing the Apollo science program was about to start in earnest but people were losing interest. Apollo Gets Complicated - New technology is added that extends the reach of the Apollo program.

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration
programme.desc: The Shuttle Program - The first re-useable spacecraft. The Challenger Disaster - Pressing launch schedules lead to carelessness and the loss of the Challenger. Return to Space - A re-designed shuttle is back in space with a redefined role.

programme.title: Trajectory - Milestones in Space Exploration
programme.desc: The Space Shuttle Matures - The Space Transportation System changes the nature of orbital missions. Complex Construction in Space - Confidence in the shuttle begins to return and engineers for get the lessons of the past.

programme.title: Beyond Earth
programme.desc: Shot over eight years and with unprecedented access, Beyond Earth: The Beginning of NewSpace, is a journey into space exploration with leading astropreneurs that shows us what is in store for mankind.

programme.desc: Before we can reach space, we must first be able to see it. Hundreds of years ago, the simple telescope was used to give us a seemingly closer vantage. Today, we use the awe-inspiring, and super powerful, Hubble Space Telescope.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Superscopes

programme.desc: Since a fire in the laundry room caused severe smoke damage inside the Bates house, how will the family handle their daily routine, since temporarily relocating to just two rooms in a hotel?

programme.desc: It’s Wedding time – but who's walking down the aisle? Love is blooming for the Bates, with Carlin finding a “special friend” in Evan. Even the married couples have big news! Will Erin and Chad's family be growing by two?

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Dead of Night
programme.desc: Dog's good friend and fellow bondsman Chris is running out of time. He has only days to find his fugitive or risk losing his business. In his hunt Dog confronts duplicitous tipsters, vicious attack dogs, and hostile neighbors.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Best of . . .

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Montrose Files: The Million Dollar Man Pt. 1
programme.desc: Dog launches a high stake hunt through the desolate and dangerous mountain landscape of western Colorado in pursuit of a gun-loving survivalist with a million dollar bond on his head. Will Dog's plan of using brains over brawn work?

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Montrose Files: The Million Dollar Man Pt. 2
programme.desc: Once in Montrose, Dog discovers that the million dollar fugitive is not the young bondsman's only problem. Dog and Beth make it their mission to both clean up the mess and teach him the fundamentals of bondsmanship.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Montrose Files: Round the Clock
programme.desc: Dog is committed to saving his new friend's bail bonding business, and now must race against time to bring a rogues gallery to justice in the High Sierra mountain town of Montrose, CO.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Montrose Files: And Then There Were None
programme.desc: With four outlaws still on the lam, Dog sets out to bring 'em in. As day turns into night and with the darkness and the danger mounting, an undaunted Dog and team plan late night hits on the riskiest of locations--their targets' homes.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Oh Brother, Where Art Thou?
programme.desc: With a long record of violence and abuse and weighing in at over 200lbs, Dog's target for the day does not sound like a gentle giant. When the trail grows cold Dog turns up the heat on the fugitive's brother and sister.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Cap and Gown
programme.desc: Friend of the family, Kili, is joining the team to help track down a runner on the Hawaiian island of Maui. This is not the only thing on their schedule, because after the hunt, Kili has to hurry off to his college graduation ceremony!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: And Baby Makes Three
programme.desc: Leland has to attend a Lamaze class before he can join the hunt--another Chapman is on the way! But when Dog starts to go after this accused jewelry thief without his fastest son, he learns that this fugitive puts the "R" in runner.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Tender Trap
programme.desc: When Dog discovers today's prey is a notorious ladies man, he knows just how to lure him in. The trap includes a suggestive phone call, a motel rendezvous, and a crew of bounty hunters waiting in the next room ready to break up the party!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Greed is Good
programme.desc: Today's fugitive is accused of assaulting a police officer, so Dog and the team are not taking any chances. Dog has to play on his target's greed and deploy some modern technology to set a trap for this runner.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Baby's Back in Town
programme.desc: Dog tries to nab a fugitive, named Wayne, by calling and telling him that he's won a new vacuum cleaner and he should stick around to get it. Dog then sends his daughter, Lyssa, to "deliver" the vacuum cleaner and lure Wayne out of his house.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Jonah is Missing
programme.desc: Dog and the team search for Jonah, a violent and desperate criminal facing?20 years in jail. The trail goes stale when Dog runs into evasive family members and an angry girlfriend.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Suga On My Cuffs
programme.desc: Dog and the team go after Kandice, AKA Candy, AKA Suga, a stripper who didn't make her court appearance. They convince one of her friends to lure her to a supermarket parking lot, where Dog has an easy time fetching the fetching young thing. But then.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mothers and Daughters
programme.desc: Dog and Beth take on the heartbreaking case of Rachel. Rachel's mom bailed her out of jail on condition that she go to AA meetings and stick to a curfew. But Rachel hasn't kept up her end of the bargain, and now her mother wants her back to jail.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Dog Is Smokin'
programme.desc: Dog is trying to cut down on smoking, but it's not easy with his high-stress job. Today, he must track down Walter, a fugitive who believes that the Canadian military has planted a chip in his tooth that allows him to communicate with his van.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: You Snooze, You Lose
programme.desc: Beth designs a luxurious new office for the team and shows it off to Dog, but the bounty hunter is more interested in starting his hunt for Federico, who's been revoked for missing court dates and generally running amuck.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Judgment Day
programme.desc: Dog goes on his a case, which involves Bobby, who's been on parole for three months pending sentencing on an assault charge. Bobby's girlfriend wants him back in jail, and Dog agrees that the Bobby needs to be behind bars.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Moms & Dads
programme.desc: Dog pursues two people whose lives have been ruined by drugs. First, he tracks Mae, who traded a good home and loving family for an ice pipe. The next case involves Jude. His addiction has caused his pregnant wife to fear for her safety.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Do Unto Others
programme.desc: Dog is a rough, tough bounty hunter, but he's a softie at heart, as the two cases in this episode show.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: A Helping Hand
programme.desc: Dog answers two very different calls for help from women. In the first case, he helps Leland protect Maria, who's being threatened by her violent husband. Then Dog visit a young woman who's dying and has asked to see Dog as one of her final wishes.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Take Your Daughter to Work Day
programme.desc: Baby Lyssa, who's just turned 18 and is studying to become a bondsman, gets to do some on-the-job training when she helps Dog hunt for Wayne, who's run out on a bond for second-degree assault.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: In Sickness and In Health
programme.desc: Dog is sick as a dog, but he still must lead the hunt for a fugitive named James. James' girlfriend tries to cover for him, but Dog surprises James in his bedroom and leads him away in cuffs.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: If the Shirt Fits...
programme.desc: Beth buys Dog a shirt with an embroidered chicken, but Dog explains he only wears shirts with pictures of either Jesus or a Harley-Davidson. When it's time to go to work, the team goes after Necia, a fugitive with felony charges pending.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Thief Who Stole Christmas
programme.desc: It's Christmas day, and Dog sets out to nab Raymond, who robs to support his ice habit, and give him a little Christmas gift - shiny new handcuffs.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Rock-a-Bye Bounty
programme.desc: Dog and Beth must go after their former housekeeper, Lisa, who's jumped bond. They know this case will be tricky because Lisa knows everyone in the family. Luckily, Beth's nephew, Jason, is visiting and is quickly put to work as the bait.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Father-Hood
programme.desc: Before Tim heads out for a tough day of bounty hunting, he likes to get in a little quality time with his daughter, Summer Rain.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Cops and Criminals
programme.desc: After giving a rousing speech to an audience of enthusiastic grade-schoolers, Dog catches up with an old friend, Sheriff Tommy Cayetano, to talk business. Dog's got a tough fugitive, named Mia, to catch and Tommy is happy to lend a hand.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Cupid in Cuffs
programme.desc: It's the day before Valentine's Day and love is in the air at Da Kine Bail Bonds--but not for Tapi who has failed to appear in court on theft charges. Dog's plan is to have Leland knock on Tapi's door with a Valentine's gift to draw her out.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bonds of Love
programme.desc: Dog and Beth are finally getting married! They've been together for more than ten years but Dog is determined, as he puts it, to "marry his common law wife the Christian way.".

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: To Love and to Cherish
programme.desc: Dog and Beth are off to the Big Island for their wedding. They hope to relax for a few days but it turns out Leland has a fugitive he needs to catch and despite the time limit, neither Dog nor Beth can resist the opportunity to catch a fugitive.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bustin' with Justin
programme.desc: Dog and the team must deal with misleading informants, belligerent boaters, and angry drunks when they go after Kimberly, a traffic offender with over 20 violations. And if that isn't enough, Dog has another problem - Duane Lee is sick.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Run Fugitive, Run
programme.desc: When the team hunts for Steven, a fugitive with a history of domestic abuse, they seek help from his girlfriend, who's been a victim of his abuse. Meanwhile, Beth trains for a 5K race to help raise awareness about domestic abuse.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Vegas or Bust
programme.desc: Dog is going to be the keynote speaker at the annual Profession Bail Agents convention in Las Vegas, but before he leaves he's got to clear two cases from his docket - Heidi and Stephanie.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Playing Possum
programme.desc: Tim's got a big problem. Owen has failed to appear in court. He's on bond for serious drug charges and now Tim could lose $30,000 if he doesn't catch Owen. With Dog's help he tries to track down the co-signer but they come up dry.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Rainy Day Woman
programme.desc: It's been raining for days and the team is going a little stir crazy, but Dog has the cure; a good hunt. Maui has failed to appear on a drug charge and the team has just one lead. She was recently spotted during a bust at a local chop shop garage.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Ticket to Ride
programme.desc: Dog decides it's time to outfit the Da Kine crew with new SUVs. After a quick visit to their local dealership, they go after Jasmine, a woman whose criminal record includes over 37 arrests for everything from drug promotion to assault.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mother Knows Best
programme.desc: Dog has two fugitives to catch, and he gets help from the unlikeliest sources - the fugitives' mothers. First, Ginger's mother wants to revoke her daughter's bond. Then, Brandon's mother decides to revoke his bond because Brandon has an ice habit.
